column12: Did not check ADC 2 during initial QA
fused with new master configuration file
TP5 to backplate had resistance of 1-2 ohms, due to extra globs of solder on back, fixed with capton tape.

TP5 to backplate res < 1ohm, caused power to shut off when fusing; Took apart applied more thermal paste then reassembled, found a scratch on the back of the DCB and a bent pin on the master optical mezzanine slot; Succeeded in fusing board.  Returning to manufacturer to fix bent pin (J7, pin 58)
GBTx not being detected after writing master txt, not going to waitDESlLock, alternating between different statuses -> goes away when 2v5 powered
MC Mezzanine difficult to install, need to go on new backplate
After writing GBTx not going to waitDESLock, alternating statuses -> goes away when 2v5 powered
careful when handling, lots of thermal paste
goes to idle after writing master.txt when 2v5 is not powered.  Otherwise, locks normally.
GBTx #3 reports errors instantly, test pattern and memory monitoring looks good
problem with fusing, the computer does not recognize the board as connected
Originally had jumper J13 in wrong place (shorting the board) and was run with 3.3V, fixed jumper position and proceeded to fuse and complete PRBS without problem
invalid input sequence for GBT 2,3/ saw data valid not being pulled up
problem with fusing, the computer does not recognize the board as connected
